#MEM id=using-git-worktrees source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/superpowers/using-git-worktrees/SKILL.md
M|using-git-worktrees|name: using-git-worktrees
M|using-git-worktrees|description: >-
M|using-git-worktrees|Use when starting feature work that needs isolation from current workspace or before executing implementation plans - creates isolated git worktrees with smart directory selection and safety verificat
M|using-git-worktrees|version: 1.0.0
M|using-git-worktrees|platforms: []
M|using-git-worktrees|metadata:
M|using-git-worktrees|hermes:
M|using-git-worktrees|tags: [dev, nextjs, typescript, architecture, vercel, api-routes, build, productivity]
M|using-git-worktrees|Git worktrees create isolated workspaces sharing the same repository, allowing work on multiple branches simultaneously without switching.
M|using-git-worktrees|**Core principle:** Systematic directory selection + safety verification = reliable isolation.
M|using-git-worktrees|**Announce at start:** "I'm using the using-git-worktrees skill to set up an isolated workspace."
M|using-git-worktrees|Follow this priority order:
M|using-git-worktrees|```bash
M|using-git-worktrees|ls -d .worktrees 2>/dev/null     # Preferred (hidden)
M|using-git-worktrees|ls -d worktrees 2>/dev/null      # Alternative
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|**If found:** Use that directory. If both exist, `.worktrees` wins.
M|using-git-worktrees|```bash
M|using-git-worktrees|grep -i "worktree.*director" CLAUDE.md 2>/dev/null
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|**If preference specified:** Use it without asking.
M|using-git-worktrees|If no directory exists and no CLAUDE.md preference:
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|No worktree directory found. Where should I create worktrees?
M|using-git-worktrees|1. .worktrees/ (project-local, hidden)
M|using-git-worktrees|2. ~/.config/superpowers/worktrees/<project-name>/ (global location)
M|using-git-worktrees|Which would you prefer?
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|**MUST verify directory is ignored before creating worktree:**
M|using-git-worktrees|```bash
M|using-git-worktrees|git check-ignore -q .worktrees 2>/dev/null || git check-ignore -q worktrees 2>/dev/null
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|**If NOT ignored:**
M|using-git-worktrees|Per Jesse's rule "Fix broken things immediately":
M|using-git-worktrees|1. Add appropriate line to .gitignore
M|using-git-worktrees|2. Commit the change
M|using-git-worktrees|3. Proceed with worktree creation
M|using-git-worktrees|**Why critical:** Prevents accidentally committing worktree contents to repository.
M|using-git-worktrees|No .gitignore verification needed - outside project entirely.
M|using-git-worktrees|```bash
M|using-git-worktrees|project=$(basename "$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)")
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|```bash
M|using-git-worktrees|case $LOCATION in
M|using-git-worktrees|.worktrees|worktrees)
M|using-git-worktrees|path="$LOCATION/$BRANCH_NAME"
M|using-git-worktrees|;;
M|using-git-worktrees|~/.config/superpowers/worktrees/*)
M|using-git-worktrees|path="~/.config/superpowers/worktrees/$project/$BRANCH_NAME"
M|using-git-worktrees|;;
M|using-git-worktrees|esac
M|using-git-worktrees|git worktree add "$path" -b "$BRANCH_NAME"
M|using-git-worktrees|cd "$path"
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|Auto-detect and run appropriate setup:
M|using-git-worktrees|```bash
M|using-git-worktrees|if [ -f package.json ]; then npm install; fi
M|using-git-worktrees|if [ -f Cargo.toml ]; then cargo build; fi
M|using-git-worktrees|if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi
M|using-git-worktrees|if [ -f pyproject.toml ]; then poetry install; fi
M|using-git-worktrees|if [ -f go.mod ]; then go mod download; fi
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|Run tests to ensure worktree starts clean:
M|using-git-worktrees|```bash
M|using-git-worktrees|npm test
M|using-git-worktrees|cargo test
M|using-git-worktrees|pytest
M|using-git-worktrees|go test ./...
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|**If tests fail:** Report failures, ask whether to proceed or investigate.
M|using-git-worktrees|**If tests pass:** Report ready.
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|Worktree ready at <full-path>
M|using-git-worktrees|Tests passing (<N> tests, 0 failures)
M|using-git-worktrees|Ready to implement <feature-name>
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|| Situation | Action |
M|using-git-worktrees||-----------|--------|
M|using-git-worktrees|| `.worktrees/` exists | Use it (verify ignored) |
M|using-git-worktrees|| `worktrees/` exists | Use it (verify ignored) |
M|using-git-worktrees|| Both exist | Use `.worktrees/` |
M|using-git-worktrees|| Neither exists | Check CLAUDE.md → Ask user |
M|using-git-worktrees|| Directory not ignored | Add to .gitignore + commit |
M|using-git-worktrees|| Tests fail during baseline | Report failures + ask |
M|using-git-worktrees|| No package.json/Cargo.toml | Skip dependency install |
M|using-git-worktrees|- **Problem:** Worktree contents get tracked, pollute git status
M|using-git-worktrees|- **Fix:** Always use `git check-ignore` before creating project-local worktree
M|using-git-worktrees|- **Problem:** Creates inconsistency, violates project conventions
M|using-git-worktrees|- **Fix:** Follow priority: existing > CLAUDE.md > ask
M|using-git-worktrees|- **Problem:** Can't distinguish new bugs from pre-existing issues
M|using-git-worktrees|- **Fix:** Report failures, get explicit permission to proceed
M|using-git-worktrees|- **Problem:** Breaks on projects using different tools
M|using-git-worktrees|- **Fix:** Auto-detect from project files (package.json, etc.)
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|You: I'm using the using-git-worktrees skill to set up an isolated workspace.
M|using-git-worktrees|[Check .worktrees/ - exists]
M|using-git-worktrees|[Verify ignored - git check-ignore confirms .worktrees/ is ignored]
M|using-git-worktrees|[Create worktree: git worktree add .worktrees/auth -b feature/auth]
M|using-git-worktrees|[Run npm install]
M|using-git-worktrees|[Run npm test - 47 passing]
M|using-git-worktrees|Worktree ready at /Users/jesse/myproject/.worktrees/auth
M|using-git-worktrees|Tests passing (47 tests, 0 failures)
M|using-git-worktrees|Ready to implement auth feature
M|using-git-worktrees|```
M|using-git-worktrees|**Never:**
M|using-git-worktrees|- Create worktree without verifying it's ignored (project-local)
M|using-git-worktrees|- Skip baseline test verification
M|using-git-worktrees|- Proceed with failing tests without asking
M|using-git-worktrees|- Assume directory location when ambiguous
M|using-git-worktrees|- Skip CLAUDE.md check
M|using-git-worktrees|**Always:**
M|using-git-worktrees|- Follow directory priority: existing > CLAUDE.md > ask
M|using-git-worktrees|- Verify directory is ignored for project-local
M|using-git-worktrees|- Auto-detect and run project setup
M|using-git-worktrees|- Verify clean test baseline
